title: Grateful Dead Live at Alpine Valley Music Theatre on 1982-08-08
lineage: Playback: Nakamichi LX-5 -> Tascam DR680 @ 24/48Processing:SD->Audacity (Windows 7)-> CDWav editor ->TLH (flac)Taped by: Executive Crew Kyle Holbrook & Phil SchumanTransferred by Kyle Holbrook
taper: Executive Crew Kyle Holbrook & Phil Schuman
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, They Love Each Other, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Loser-> Little Red Rooster, Brown Eyed Women, Looks Like Rain, Peggy-O, Samson & Delilah

Set 2

Far From Me-> Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Estimated Prophet-> Drums*-> The Other One**-> Not Fade Away**-> Wharf Rat**-> Good Lovin'**, E: Satisfaction**-> E: Brokedown Palace**

*W Zakir Hussain, **Other artist(s): with John Cippolina

reviews.review_text:
What a show This is a very fun show. Check out Jerry at around the 11 minute mark of "Fire" all of a sudden he kicks it up another notch and is like a dog tryin to catch its tail around and around faster and faster.Is maybe one of the hottest endings to Fire on the Mountain.  Do your self a favor and check it out.
 Everything else is hot hot hot too. They were rippin during this tour. Glad I made it.

TLEO Tipped off by the post on the forum.   Poster was right, Jerry's solo in they love each other is really creative, out of the ordinary, smoking hot.   Drills the landing back into the verse too.  One of those that would have you looking at your buddies in appreciation if you were lucky enough to be there live....
